"Ignore them." sez Howard}
^-|CP||FP||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Two students happened to write to me this week about what to do when so-called experts publicly criticize their bridge. I suspect this is a problem that many students encounter from time to time. Here is what I wrote back:|
PG| ***** 149 ***** |


AT|

My best advice is to ignore them, hard as that may be. Unsolicited advice, particularly in public, is very discourteous, and my number 1 rule in selecting people to play with is that they MUST be courteous. It is ok to discuss a hand in a non-accusatory way, but, even if someone thinks you made a mistake, it is not appropriate to belittle you in any way. And most of the time these people don't know what they are talking about. If you think they might have a legitimate point and you are wondering about it, then feel free to ask me or anyone else whose opinion you value, but don't waste your time arguing with them.|
PG| ***** 150 ***** |


AT|

Here is a story of what happened to me at a live club. I am sometimes asked to fill in when there is an odd person who needs a partner. On this particular occasion, I was playing with someone who, having played against her before, I thought was reasonably good. |
PG| ***** 151 ***** |


AT|

However, the auction went 1C-P-1S-P-2H by her. Now naturally I thought she had a reverse. But it turned out that she had a balanced 19 HCP with 4 hearts and 3 clubs, so her correct call was 2N. We ended up in 6C in a 4-3- fit, (I had 4 clubs and a good hand.) I didn't say anything after the hand until she told me my 6C bid was "stupid" because she might only have 3 clubs. |
PG| ***** 152 ***** |


AT|

Now remember, I am a pickup partner doing her a favor. Even then, although of course I was annoyed, all I said was that most people play that when they reverse they promise 5+ in their first suit, so we had a misunderstanding. She said I didn't know what I was talking about. |
PG| ***** 153 ***** |


AT|

The real point I am trying to make is notice the appropriate tone I used in discussing the hand vs. the inappropriate way she discussed the hand.|
PG| ***** 154 ***** |


AT|

"Place them on our Enemy List.", sez the |CP|1|AT|Movie Maker|CP||AT|.|
PG| ***** 155 ***** |


